properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 9 at 3:50AM PST until February 10 at 4:00AM PST by NWS Sacramento CA
properties.description:
...Strong North to East Wind Today...

.Period of strong north to east wind expected over portions of
interior Northern California today into tonight. Highest wind
speeds are forecast for later this morning into the afternoon in
the Delta area, and along the west side of the Sacramento Valley
extending into the Coastal Range. Areas of strong wind are also
possible over ridges and through favorably oriented canyons of the
Sierra Nevada. Wind speeds decrease tonight in the Central
Valley, but remain windy in the mountains into Monday morning.

* WHAT...For the High Wind Warning period, north wind 30 to 45
mph with local gusts up to 60 mph. For the Wind Advisory period,
north to northwest wind 15 to 35 mph with local gusts up to 50
mph.

* WHERE...Carquinez Strait and Delta County.

* WHEN...Wind Advisory in effect until 6 AM PST. High Wind Warning
in effect between 6 AM PST and 4 PM PST this afternoon. Wind
Advisory again in effect from 4 PM this afternoon to 4 AM PST
Monday.

* IMPACTS...Northerly wind may cause downed trees in the Delta
region due to non-prevailing wind direction. Power outages are
also possible and travel will be difficult, especially for high
profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
